    <briefdescription>
<para>The <ref refid="structDali_1_1WindowDimInfo" kindref="compound">WindowDimInfo</ref> structure contains information for dimming effect applied for window or related region. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This structure is used to configure dimming effects when <ref refid="namespaceDali_1a8aa8c647e594b2a97f07a8acbdc40170aef9c2aaa3392278b1fe2fa46124350a9" kindref="member">WindowBlurType::BEHIND</ref> is applied. Behind blur affects the area behind the window (excluding the window region itself), and this structure allows additional dimming to be applied to that blurred area for better visual contrast and user experience.</para>
<para>The dimming effect uses a color overlay with alpha transparency to darken the blurred background. This is particularly useful when the blurred background content is too bright or distracting, making it difficult to see the foreground window content clearly.</para>
<para>@SINCE_2_5.5 </para>
    </detaileddescription>
